    "type": "SensitivityAnalysis",
    "name": "Tibial tray micromotion sensitivity to bone modulus and interface friction",
    "description": "A one-at-a-time sensitivity study varied cancellous bone elastic modulus over ±30% of the nominal value (0.4–0.9 GPa) and interface friction coefficient over the range 0.3–0.7, finding that peak micromotion at the anterior keel varied by up to 18% with bone modulus and 12% with friction coefficient; the composite worst-case combination was identified as low modulus and low friction, and this configuration was adopted as the bounding scenario for the acceptance criterion evaluation."
  },
