      "type": "OperatingEnvelope",
      "name": "Physiological loading envelope for TKA tibial tray fixation assessment",
      "description": "Operating bounds: axial compressive force 1000–3000 N (1.4–4.2× body weight for 70 kg patient); anteroposterior shear force 100–600 N; torsional moment 0–15 N·m; flexion angle 0–120°; loading frequency 0.5–1.5 Hz (gait cycle). Tibial tray geometry: stem diameter 8–14 mm, keel depth 20–35 mm. Interface gap tolerance: initial micromotion acceptance threshold ≤ 150 µm per ISO 14879-1 fixation criterion."
    }
  },
